author: Beniaminek
title: Mmmmmmonster fun
review: This set shocked me! Zero finished parts that replace 10 smaller ones. Durable strong connections that withstand the worst off-road conditions. He drives forward, backward, and even up. He will come under every piece of furniture and finally get on it. Although you can't see any multi-link chassis, the car is well cushioned and behaves terribly realistically on a hard surface of a tile or table. Generally a great car.

author: ARandomLegoFan
title: A literal monster truck
review:
Part 1. The monster truck.

The monster truck is ya know. Monster styled. It has eyes and a nose on the hood and the front has teeth. The side has nothing going on and the back has two exhausts and a gap unfortunately. The truck bed has more teeth. The monster truck also has great ground clearance but no suspension.

Part 2. the figure.

The figure is unnamed and has an exclusive torso print. also I'm pretty sure his lime legs our uncommon.

Pros.

Exclusive prints,rare parts and great playability.

Cons.

Gaps in the rear.
